@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{avy-extras.el} extends @samp{avy}, the package that lets you jump to visible text in Emacs buffers using short character sequences. While @samp{avy} provides general-purpose jumping commands, it does not include line-scoped word jumping, end-of-line targeting, or mode-specific ``jump and act'' commands.

This package provides three groups of extensions:

@itemize
@item
Word-jumping commands restricted to the current visual line, with variants for the whole line, behind point, or ahead of point (@ref{Word jumping in line}).
@item
End-of-line jumping commands for lines above or below the cursor (@ref{End-of-line jumping}).
@item
Mode-specific commands that combine @code{avy-goto-line} with an action in Dired, Ebib, mu4e, Telega, and Elfeed (@ref{Mode-specific jumping}).
@item
Character-based jumping commands inspired by Vim's @samp{f} motion, with repeatable search via timeout (@ref{Character jumping}).
@end itemize

The package depends on @samp{el-patch} and @samp{use-package-extras}.

@node User options
