@node @code{avy-extras-goto-char-timeout}
@section @code{avy-extras-goto-char-timeout}

@vindex avy-extras-goto-char-timeout
The user option @code{avy-extras-goto-char-timeout} controls how long the character jumping commands (@ref{Character jumping}) wait for a repeated keypress before exiting. If the same key is not pressed within this number of seconds, the search stops and the next keypress is treated as a normal command.

The default value is @code{1} (one second). A higher value gives you more time to decide whether to continue jumping; a lower value makes the command feel snappier but requires faster key presses.

The type is a number (integer or float).

